# most state schema fields should be optional to support empty documents

Documents are created empty and populated through operations. If the state schema requires fields that are not set at creation time, the initial state will violate the schema.

```graphql
// ✅ Optional fields — document can be created empty
type InvoiceState {
    recipient: String
    amount: Amount_Money
    dueDate: Date
}

// ❌ Too many required fields — empty document fails validation
type InvoiceState {
    recipient: String!
    amount: Amount_Money!
    dueDate: Date!
}
```

Use `!` only for fields that genuinely cannot be absent, like arrays (since [[arrays in state schemas must use mandatory notation]]) or fields set at document creation time.

